CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. 14, reads: "Senior Matron Honored - Mrs. Annie Williams, seated third from left, Grand Senior Matron of the State of Pennsylvania, was honored with a testimonial reception recently at the Masonic Temple, which was sponsored by Mary Ella Court, No. 6, Heroines of Jericho.  Standing, left to right: Mmes. Fannie Allen, Laura E. Talley, Mary E. White and Irene Fuller.  Seated clockwise: Mrs. Gertrude Campbell, Mrs. Luella M. Lane, Mrs. Annie Williams, Butler Jones, Assistant Worthy Joshua; Frederick Price and Mrs. Lelia Miller. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fannie Allen, Laura E. Talley, Mary E. White, Irene Fuller; seated: Gertrude Campbell, Luella M. Lane, Annie Williams, Butler Jones, Assistant Worthy Joshua, Frederick Price, and Lelia Miller gathered for reception honoring Grand Senior Matron Williams in Masonic Temple
